# Distribution-bundle control (consumed by `git archive`).
#
# `git archive` produces a consumer bundle of the EADOS factory. The bundle is the
# factory you *operate*, not this repository's own identity, so the paths below are
# stripped via `export-ignore`:
#
#   * repo-management plumbing — CI, issue/PR templates, Dependabot, CODEOWNERS
#     (.github/), the portfolio card, .gitignore, this file, and CHANGELOG.md;
#   * this repo's identity/governance docs — README.md, SECURITY.md, CONTRIBUTING.md,
#     and the i18n translations under .eados-core/docs/i18n/. The *generated* project
#     renders its own README/SECURITY from the templates (templates/README.md.tmpl,
#     templates/SECURITY.md.tmpl); CONTRIBUTING is EADOS-only governance, and the i18n
#     set translates *this* repo's README (also stripped), so it is not needed to
#     operate the factory — keeping it would also break `eados_lint` in the bundle,
#     since its freshness manifest points at the omitted root README.md.
#
# What SHIPS in the bundle:
#   * .eados-core/** — the factory (tools, templates, profiles, docs) incl.
#     .eados-core/README.md (the bundle's entry-point instructions);
#   * the agent contract — AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md / GEMINI.md (auto-loaded from root);
#   * LICENSE — kept on purpose: render.py reads it as the source for every generated
#     project's LICENSE, so removing it would yield license-less projects.
#
# Produce a bundle:  git archive --format=tar.gz --prefix=pgs-eados/ -o pgs-eados-bundle.tar.gz HEAD
# See .eados-core/docs/USAGE.md "Distribution bundle" for the full recipe.
#
# NOTE: patterns are anchored with a leading slash so they match only the intended
# path — .eados-core/README.md and the per-directory README.md files are NOT stripped.

/.github                export-ignore
/.portfolio.json        export-ignore
/.gitignore             export-ignore
/.gitattributes         export-ignore
/.eados-dev              export-ignore
/CHANGELOG.md           export-ignore
/README.md              export-ignore
/SECURITY.md            export-ignore
/CONTRIBUTING.md        export-ignore
/.eados-core/docs/i18n   export-ignore
# The guided installer (M9) downloads the bundle, so it is not part of it: published as
# standalone release assets, not shipped inside the factory archive.
/setup                  export-ignore

# Installer line endings, pinned regardless of the committer's platform: LF for the POSIX shebang
# scripts and for setup.ps1 (pwsh reads LF fine on every OS); CRLF for the cmd .bat shim.
setup/*.sh              text eol=lf
setup/*.command         text eol=lf
setup/*.ps1             text eol=lf
setup/*.bat             text eol=crlf
